# pbpad WiFi credentials — EXAMPLE / TEMPLATE
#
# Copy this to the Pi (NOT into the repo) and fill in real values:
#     scp conf/pbpad-wifi.conf.example pi@<host>:~/.pbpad-wifi.conf
#     ssh pi@<host> "chmod 600 ~/.pbpad-wifi.conf"
# then edit ~/.pbpad-wifi.conf. setup.sh reads it and preloads the networks
# into NetworkManager. The real file is git-ignored and never committed.
#
# Format: one network per line, pipe-separated —  SSID|password|priority
#   - priority is optional (default 10); higher priority wins when both are in range
#   - blank lines and lines starting with # are ignored

My Home Network|your-wifi-password|10
My Home Network 5GHz|your-wifi-password|10
